ication/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format": "dash-1456468956077123v - 1080x1920 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by aaronvartiainen0", "description": "This is not a science channel. This is an experience channel.", "duration": 179.442, "timestamp": 1770036933, "uploader_id": "6720734023", "uploader": "Aaron Vartiainen", "channel": "aaronvartiainen0", "like_count": 30155, "comment_count": 907, "comments": [{"author": "starewiczrzegorz", "author_id": "16163447246", "id": "18077737709564992", "text": "I think you might mean something else, but to me 100% of what we perceive is made up by our mind. We can assume the world and reality and matter all exist and we can assume that they exist in an objective definable state; then our perception can only receive a fraction of that state. Some animals see more colors than we do, some animals sense more sound, echolocate, smell more smells, what else is it that we can't perceive? Time itself is extremely weird to perceive. Maybe there could be another dimension of sorts, that we're completely missing, either something 'metaphysical' or more like a 4th dimension of space, or something antimatter related.", "timestamp": 1775042235}, {"author": "publice_activae_singula", "author_id": "77339985512", "id": "18344496103212455", "text": "You saw what you needed to, to help you comprehend your experience.", "timestamp": 1774814645}, {"author": "lvmacht", "author_id": "65067562957", "id": "17970392265035242", "text": "I still see everything as tiny dots", "timestamp": 1774560812}], "thumbnails": [{"url": "https://scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/627033662_3037556839786810_4623751053857063578_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6ImltYWdlX3VybGdlbi42NDB4MTEzNi5zZHIuZjcxODc4LmRlZmF1bHRfY292ZXJfZnJhbWUuYzIifQ&_nc_ht=scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=110&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gESD209XyTOUWaE2